Broken Authentication

- Brute-force login endpoints- Use invalid/expired tokens- Replay old tokens

- Account takeover- Unauthorized access

- Implement MFA- Apply rate limiting- Enforce token expiration

2Ô∏è‚É£

Broken Object Level Authorization (BOLA)

- Modify object ID in API (e.g., /user/123 ‚Üí /user/124)

- Access to other users' data

- Enforce object-level access checks- Use UUIDs

3Ô∏è‚É£

Excessive Data Exposure

- Analyze API responses- Use tools like Burp Suite, OWASP ZAP

- Leakage of sensitive or internal data

- Filter response data on server- Avoid exposing internal fields

4Ô∏è‚É£

Lack of Rate Limiting

- Send bulk requests rapidly (DoS, brute-force)

- Resource exhaustion- Credential brute-force

- Apply rate limiting per IP/token- Monitor traffic patterns

5Ô∏è‚É£

Mass Assignment

- Send extra parameters (e.g., isAdmin=true)

- Privilege escalation- Unauthorized changes

- Use property whitelisting- Validate input schema

